tion-fun-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexploratory%20arts%20curriculum%3C%2Fa%3E%20rooted%20in%20African-American%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20I%20introduced%20the%20boys%20to%20the%20music%20of%20Fela%20Kuti%20and%20John%20Coltrane%20and%20the%20art%20of%20Jacob%20Lawrence%2C%20Romare%20Bearden%2C%20and%20Jean-Michel%20Basquiat.%20We'd%20attempt%20our%20own%20mixed-media%20collages%20and%20paint%20with%20watercolors%20on%20the%20floor%20while%20the%20polyrhythms%20of%20Afrobeat%20music%20filled%20our%20kitchen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20were%20toddlers%2C%20I%20was%20their%20teacher.%20I'd%20structure%20their%20days%20tightly%20with%20breakfast%2C%20a%20lesson%20of%20some%20sort%2C%20and%20a%20morning%20outing%20to%20a%20museum%2C%20forest%20trail%20walk%2C%20or%20errands%20with%20me%20before%20going%20back%20home%20for%20lunch.%20Then%2C%20I'd%20put%20them%20down%20for%20their%20afternoon%20nap%2C%20during%20which%20I'd%20work%20on%20projects%20for%20my%20consulting%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20touring%20several%20day%20care%20facilities%20and%20even%20using%20one%20for%20a%20few%20months.%20But%20ultimately%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20both%20decided%20the%20boys%20were%20better%20off%20at%20home%20with%20me%2C%20where%20I%20could%20more%20closely%20oversee%20their%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20obsessed%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20them%20learning%20and%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20ahead%26quot%3B%20even%20before%20they%20officially%20started%20school.%20When%20my%20kids%20were%202%20and%203%2C%20I'd%20buy%20the%20Lego%20bricks%20kit%2C%20puzzles%2C%20and%20coloring%20books%20designed%20for%20the%204-%20and%205-year-olds.%20I%20was%20always%20pushing%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-parents-set-their-kids-up-for-success-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereach%20beyond%20average%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20I%20wanted%20them%20to%20be%20exceptional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they