0gold%20star%20for%20thinking%20of%20everything%20myself%2C%20I%20regularly%20reach%20out%20to%20copy%20their%20homework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d08ed66-ce7c-4380-aea6-a84493322a45%5C%22%3EI%20learned%20it's%20OK%20to%20ask%20other%20parents%20for%20help%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20girl-mom%20network%20has%20shared%20hand-me-down%20winter%20coats%2C%20barely-worn%20Easter%20dresses%2C%20and%20pediatric%20specialist%20recommendations.%20They've%20passed%20on%20enrollment%20links%20to%20Saturday%20soccer%20and%20their%20copious%20notes%20on%20elementary%20school%20options.%20They've%20done%20the%20homework%20to%20find%20the%20best%203-year-old%20ballet%20class%3B%20they've%20already%20found%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwearing-braids-self-love-practice-from-my-dad-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehair%20braider%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20makes%20house%20calls%20and%20is%20good%20with%20squirming%20toddlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20feel%20guilty%20asking%20for%20recommendations%2C%20like%20I%20was%20cutting%20in%20line.%20I've%20always%20pulled%20my%20own%20weight%20and%20done%20more%20than%20expected%3B%20I%20never%20wanted%20to%20be%20perceived%20as%20a%20slacker.%20But%20I've%20learned%20relying%20on%20my%20network%20to%20hook%20me%20up%20doesn't%20make%20me%20lazy%2C%20unserious%2C%20or%20checked%20out%20as%20a%20parent.%20Their%20support%20keeps%20me%20from%20running%20myself%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%2030s%2C%20I%20was%20terrified%20that%20if%20I%20alone%20somehow%20failed%20to%20overwork%20and%20overachieve%20as%20a%20parent%2C%20I%20would%20hold%20my%20kids%20back.%20But%20my%20mindset%20has%20evolved%20as%20I've%20matured%2C%20so%20now%20I%20give%20myself%20grace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20older%20kids%20were%20small%2C%20I%20was%20parenting%20under%20the%20gun%2C%20as%20if%20so%20much%20was%20at%20stake%20if%20I%20didn't%20push%20them%20to%20achieve.%20I%20think%20a%20big%20part%20of%20my%20self-worth%20was%20tied%20up%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fovercoming-parenting-shame-therapy-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20well%20I%20performed%20in%20motherhood%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Each%20of%20their%20accomplishments%20was%20like%20a%20gold%20star%20%E2%80%94%20proof%20that%20I%20was%20indeed%20a%20good%20mother.%20If%20they%20weren't%20ahead%2C%20or%20at%20least%20on%20track%2C%20I%20was%20failing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that's%20largely%20because%20I%20viewed%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Bmy%20greatest%20achievements%26quot%3B%20and%20their%20own%20achievements%20as%20necessary%20currency%20for%20their%20future%20happiness%20and%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realize%20that%20the%20way%20the%20world%20is%20set%20up%2C%20a%20level%20of%20achievement%20is%20necessary%20but%20perhaps%20not%20required%20for%20the%20type%20of%20happiness%20or%20success%20they%20will%20eventually%20seek.%20They%20are%20not%20me.%20We%20are%20alike%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20but%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20we%20are%20different.%20They%20tell%20me%20they%20appreciate%20the%20early%20push%2C%20but%20did%20they%20need%20that%20to%20get%20where%20they%20are%3F%20I'm%20not%20so%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amanda%20Miller%20Littlejohn%20with%20her%20sons%20and%20daughter%20at%20the%20beach%2C%20they%20are%20smiling%20in%20the%20sun%20and%20standing%20on%20the%20sand.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66996cf849138fa6f6e39e21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20learned%20it's%20OK%20to%20ask%20for%20recommendations%20from%20friends%20and%20other%20parents%20while%20parenting%20her%20daughter.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Amanda%20Miller%20Littlejohn%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cc66fba-783f-4e18-ba80-b175e9594e8f%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20have%20to%20overwork%20to%20be%20considered%20a%20good%20mom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20more%20laid%20back%20this%20time%20around%20means%20I'm%20more%20present.%20I'm%20not%20my%20daughter's%20CEO%20or%20performance%20coach%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20just%20mommy.%20Now%2C%20I%20play%20with%20no%20agenda%3B%20every%20toy%20doesn't%20have%20to%20teach%20a%20new%20skill%2C%20and%20every%20game%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20a%20stepping%20stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20mothers%20are%20beginning%20to%20renegotiate%20the%20idea%20that%20we%20must%20pour%20every%20ounce%20of%20free%20time%20and%20effort%20into%20our%20kids%20to%20be%20considered%20%26quot%3Bgood%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20for%20us%20to%20be%20considered%20good%20mothers.%20By%20all%20means%2C%20we%20want%20them%20to%20be%20great%2C%20but%20we%20are%20also%20learning%20to%20trust%20they'll%20find%20their%20way.%20Their%20paths%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20so%20engineered%3B%20we%20can%20let%20them%20simply%20unfold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20is%203%20years%20old%20and%20not%20reading%20yet%20like%20my%20older%20kids%20were%20at%20her%20age%2C%20but%20she's%20one%20of%20the%20most%20socially%20intelligent%20people%20I%20know.%20So%2C%20instead%20of%20comparing%20her%20to%20her%20brothers%2C%20I'm%20nurturing%20her%20natural%20gifts%20and%20valuing%20her%20uniqueness.%20I'm%20learning%20to%20parent%20her%20as%20a%20person%2C%20not%20as%20a%20project%20for%20extra%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20that%20I%20strive%20to%20do%20the%20bare%20minimum%20as%20a%20mother%20now%2C%20but%20I%20realize%20overworking%20isn't%20practical%20or%20required%20at%20this%20stage%20in%20my%20life.%20I've%20already%20done%20the%20work%2C%20and%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20kids%20are%20all%20right.%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20burn%20myself%20out%20for%20them%20to%20be%20OK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foverachieving-parent-burnout-learned-ask-help-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%