ny%20government%20regulation%20of%20technology%20and%20venture%20capital.%20Scrappy%20little%20startups%2C%20the%20manifesto%20asserts%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Bthe%20vanguard%20of%20American%20technology%20supremacy.%26quot%3B%20They%20fuel%20hypergrowth%2C%20improve%20everyone's%20quality%20of%20life%2C%20and%20guarantee%20American%20military%20superiority%20and%20global%20stability.%20The%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELittle%20Tech%20agenda%20also%20includes%20a%20surprising%20hat%20tip%20to%20the%20defense%20industry%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffailure-silicon-valley-bank-myth-american-west-pioneer-frontier-technology-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20original%20funders%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-defense-tech-vcs-to-know-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereliable%20customers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20startup%2C%26quot%3B%20Andreessen%20has%20written%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20what%20happens%20when%20a%20plucky%20group%20of%20outcasts%20and%20misfits%20comes%20together%20with%20a%20dream%2C%20ambition%2C%20courage%2C%20and%20a%20particular%20set%20of%20skills%20%E2%80%94%20to%20build%20something%20new%20in%20the%20world%2C%20to%20build%20a%20product%20that%20will%20improve%20people's%20lives%2C%20and%20to%20build%20a%20company%20that%20may%20go%20on%20to%20create%20many%20more%20new%20things%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%20And%20Trump%2C%20he%20believes%2C%20is%20the%20man%20who%20will%20prevent%20big%20government%20from%20getting%20in%20the%20way%20of%20these%20daring%20visionaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20listening%20to%20Andreessen%20explain%20his%20political%20change%20of%20heart%2C%20I%20came%20away%20convinced%20of%20two%20things%3A%20(1)%20His%20Trumpiness%20doesn't%20make%20much%20sense%2C%20and%20(2)%20neither%20does%20his%20Little%20Tech%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20I%20know%20this%3F%20Because%20for%20the%20past%2020%20years%2C%20I've%20been%20reading%20a%20smart%2C%20prolific%20tech%20blogger%20named%20Marc%20Andreessen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Andreessen%20and%20Horowitz%20formed%20their%20venture-capital%20firm%20in%202009%2C%20Andreessen%20was%20an%20incisive%20observer%20of%20Silicon%20Valley.%20And%20in%20those%20days%2C%20before%20he%20had%20so%20much%20money%20in%20the%20game%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20080229071047%2Fhttp%3A%2Fblog.pmarca.com%2F2007%2F06%2Fthe_truth_about.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewarned%20us%20against%20falling%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20hyperbole%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20he's%20now%20spewing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20then%2C%20Andreesen's%20concept%20of%20what%20constituted%20a%20startup%20was%20a%20lot%20simpler.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20many%20fine%20businesses%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20them%20highly%20profitable%2C%20and%20very%20satisfying%20to%20run%20%E2%80%94%20that%20do%20not%20have%20leverage%20in%20their%20model%20that%20makes%20them%20suitable%20for%20venture%20capital%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20Meaning%2C%20in%20plain%20English%2C%20that%20what%20constituted%20a%20startup%20worthy%20of%20VC%20backing%20was%20the%20ability%20to%20get%20a%2010x%20return%20on%20investments%20in%20five%20years%20%E2%80%94%20to%20make%20something%20once%2C%20like%20a%20piece%20of%20software%20or%20a%20website%2C%20and%20then%20sell%20it%20to%201%2C000%20businesses%20or%20millions%20of%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20it.%20That's%20all%20a%20venture-backed%20startup%20should%20be%2C%20according%20to%20Andreessen.%20It's%20not%20Captain%20America's%20shield%20or%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20Andreesen%20(meaning%20the%20current%20bloated%20billionaire%20model)%20also%20contradicts%20Little%20Andreessen%20(the%20earlier%2C%20leaner%20blogger)%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20regulation.%20His%20partner%2C%20Horowitz%2C%20recently%20wrote%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fa16z.com%2Fpolitics-and-the-future%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emain%20risk%20to%20American%20tech%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20by%20extension%20American%20global%20hegemony%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bmisguided%20regulatory%20policy.%26quot%3B%20Government%20needs%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20way%20of%20%26quot%3Bdecentralized%20technologies%26quot%3B%20like%20AI%2C%20biotech%2C%20and%20blockchain%20and%20focus%20its%20energies%20on%20%26quot%3Bthe%20centralized%2C%20monopoly-enabling%20technologies%20of%20web%202%20and%20the%20industrial-era%20financial%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2015%20years%20ago%2C%20Andreessen%20told%20us%20that's%20the%20wrong%20way%20to%20think%20about%20the%20internet.%20%26quot%3BWeb%202.0%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20picked%20up%20as%20a%20term%20by%20the%20entrepreneurial%20community%20and%20its%20corollaries%20in%20venture%20capital%2C%20the%20press%2C%20analysts%2C%20large%20media%20and%20Internet%20companies%2C%20and%20Wall%20Street%20to%20describe%20a%20theoretical%20new%20category%20of%20startup%20companies.%26quot%3B%20But%20it%20was%20just%20branding%2C%20he%20explained.%20There%20aren't%20%26quot%3Bspaces%26quot%3B%20or%20ecosystems.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20product%20is%20compelling%20to%20the%20market%2C%20it%20will%20succeed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20product%20is%20not%20compelling%20to%20the%20market%2C%20it%20will%20fail.%26quot%3B%20The%20issue%20isn't%20whether%20tech%20is%20good%20or%20bad%20for%20America.%20The%20issue%20is%20whether%20the%20tech%20actually%20works%20and%20fills%20a%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20fair%2C%20Andreessen%20didn't%20worry%20much%20about%20regulation%20back%20in%20the%20old%20days.%20The%20reason%2C%20he%20now%20claims%2C%20is%20that%20government%20used%20to%20leave%20Silicon%20Valley%20alone.%20On%20the%20podcast%20he%20said%20Democrats%20used%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bpro-tech%2C%20they%20were%20pro-startup%2C%20they%20were%20pro-America%20winning%20in%20tech%20markets%2C%20they%20were%20pro-entrepreneurship.%20You%20could%20be%20successful%20in%20business%2C%20you%20could%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20and%20then%20you%20give%20the%20money%20away%20in%20philanthropy%20and%20get%20enormous%20credit.%26quot%3B%20VC%20investors%20operated%20in%20a%20magical%20technolibertarian%20liminal%20space%2C%20a%20West%20wild%20enough%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20make%20tiny%20iPhones%20and%20big%20bucks.%20But%20the%20Biden%20administration%20changed%20that%2C%20Andreessen%20argues%2C%20by%20trying%20to%20regulate%20the%20%26quot%3Bmath%26quot%3B%20of%20AI%20and%20by%20going%20after%20Big%20Tech's%20anticompetitive%20and%20deceptive%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20Andreessen%20is%20just%20deploying%20the%20Trumpian%20trick%20of%20falsely%20idealizing%20the%20past.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20didn't%20invent%20tech%20regulation.%20It's%20just%20resuscitating%20regulatory%20practices%20that%20were%20well%20in%20play%20back%20in%20the%201990s%20and%20early%202000s.%20Like%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-1990s-antitrust-case-looms-over-apple-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20Justice%20Department%20sued%20Microsoft%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20separated%20its%20web%20browser%20from%20its%20operating%20system.%20Or%20a%20decade%20or%20so%20before%20that%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-a-look-at-the-long-history-of-atts-battles-with-the-us-government-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20government%20broke%20up%20AT%26amp%3BT%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20sparked%20a%20whole%20new%20flourishing%20of%20telecommunications%20companies.%20Enforcing%20regulations%20almost%20always%20opens%20the%20field%20to%20new%20startups%20and%20a%20diverse%20set%20of%20new%20technologies.%20Biden's%20position%20is%20basically%20that%20to%20Make%20America%20Great%20Again%2C%20we%20need%20to%20Make%20America%20Innovate%20Again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20suspect%20some%20of%20Andreessen's%20support%20of%20Trump%20is%20really%20just%20personal.%20His%20explanation%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmarchive.com%2Fan_hour_and_a_half_with_barack_obama.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhy%20he%20endorsed%20Barack%20Obama%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20basically%20boils%20down%20to%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20very%20long%20meeting%20with%20him%20and%20he%20charmed%20me.%26quot%3B%20This%20time%20around%2C%20well%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20met%20with%20Andreessen%20and%20Horowitz%2C%20but%20Joe%20Biden%20did%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20any%20rate%2C%20Andreessen's%20support%20of%20Trump%20hardly%20comes%20as%20a%20surprise.%20He%20and%20his%20fellow%20Silicon%20Valley%20investor-class%20billionaires%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-david-sacks-dinner-anti-biden-hollywood-hills-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esliding%20rightward%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20years.%20Despite%20all%20their%20highfalutin%20language%20about%20saving%20America%20through%20technological%20innovation%2C%20they're%20actually%20arguing%20%3Cem%3Eagainst%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20kind%20of%20anticompetitive%20rules%20that%20would%20enable%20innovation%20to%20flourish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20'Little%20Tech%20Agenda'%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20innovation%20or%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.techpolicy.press%2Fthe-little-tech-agenda-is-just-selfserving-nonsense%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eobserves%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20political%20scientist%20and%20tech%20analyst%20Dave%20Karpf.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20VC%20wish%20list.%20The%20investor%20class%20isn't%20clever%20enough%20to%20invest%20in%20companies%20that%20turn%20a%20profit%20by%20bringing%20useful%20products%20to%20market%20anymore.%20They%20need%20special%20treatment%20from%20the%20government%20for%20their%20bad%20investments%20to%20pay%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20his%20own%20share%20prices%20and%20dividends%2C%20Andreessen's%20biggest%20about-face%20is%20his%20refusal%20to%20take%20into%20account%20the%20larger%20consequences%20of%20supporting%20Trump.%20In%202016%2C%20Andreessen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F2016%2F6%2F14%2F11940052%2Fmarc-andreessen-donald-trump-hillary-clinton%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexplained%20his%20support%20of%20Hillary%20Clinton%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Bloomberg%20Technology%20Conference.%20He%20said%20he%20looked%20at%20four%20criteria%20for%20a%20president%3A%20science%20policy%2C%20market%20policy%2C%20trade%2C%20and%20immigration.%20He%20was%20unhappy%20with%20the%20Democrats%20for%20regulating%20GMOs%2C%20he%20said.%20But%20the%20dealbreaker%2C%20for%20him%2C%20was%20Trump's%20restrictive%20and%20racist%20immigration%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Valley%20wouldn't%20be%20here%2C%20we%20wouldn't%20be%20doing%20any%20of%20this%2C%20if%20we%20didn't%20have%20the%20amazing%20flow%20of%20immigrants%20that%20we've%20had%20in%20the%20last%2080%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Andreessen%20declared.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20idea%20of%20choking%20that%20off%20just%20makes%20me%20sick%20to%20my%20stomach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20Trump's%20immigration%20policies%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstagflation-recession-trump-policy-tariff-immigration-deportation-economy-outlook-jpmorgan-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eonly%20gotten%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eworse%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20Andreessen's%20digestion%20has%20somehow%20improved%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20writing%20about%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20on%20and%20off%2C%20since%20before%20Andreessen's%20company%20Netscape%20went%20public.%20I%20always%20thought%20that%20the%20gadgets%20and%20connections%20coming%20out%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20were%20more%20than%20just%20toys%20%E2%80%94%20that%20they%20really%20could%20presage%20a%20world%20where%20people%20had%20better%20stuff%20and%20more%20knowledge.%20I%20bought%20Silicon%20Valley's%20founding%20rhetoric.%20Tech%20would%20be%20a%20great%20democratic%20equalizer.%20Whether%20people%20got%20rich%20along%20the%20way%20seemed%20incidental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20now%20understand%20my%20mistake.%20It's%20not%20that%20Andreessen%20has%20changed%2C%20or%20that%20his%20support%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20hypocritical.%20It's%20that%20I%20didn't%20see%20that%20this%20is%20where%20Silicon%20Valley%20was%20always%20headed.%20For%20the%20people%20who%20got%20rich%20off%20tech%2C%20getting%20rich%20was%20always%20the%20point.%20By%20backing%20Trump%2C%20they're%20making%20clear%20that%20nothing%20else%20matters%20to%20them%3A%20not%20human%20rights%2C%20not%20the%20climate%20emergency%2C%20not%20women's%20reproductive%20health%2C%20not%20the%20%26quot%3Bamazing%20flow%20of%20immigrants%26quot%3B%20who%20helped%20them%20get%20rich%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20It's%20easy%20to%20scoff%20at%20the%20way%20they%20now%20claim%20to%20care%20about%20making%20America%20great.%20But%20I%20was%20a%20sucker%20for%20believing%20they%20ever%20cared%20about%20anything%20beyond%20their%20own%20self-interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarc-andreessens-endorsement-donald-trump-tech-industry-silicon-valley-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2