tml%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Profit%20Growing%2C%20Hiring%2C%20Salaries%20Not%20So%20Much%3A%20Centre's%20Message%20To%20India%20Inc%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20corporate%20sector%20in%20India%20has%20been%20posting%20impressive%20financial%20performances%2C%20but%20recruitments%20and%20salary%20growth%20of%20employees%20have%20not%20kept%20up%20with%20the%20companies'%20profit%2C%20the%20government%20has%20said%20in%20the%20Economic%20Survey%20for%202023-24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStressing%20that%20job%20creation%20happens%20mainly%20in%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20the%20government%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20financial%20performance%2C%20the%20corporate%20sector%20has%20never%20had%20it%20so%20good.%20Results%20of%20a%20sample%20of%20over%2033%2C000%C2%A0companies%20show%20that%2C%20in%20the%20three%20years%20between%20FY20%20and%20FY23%2C%20the%20profit%20before%20taxes%20of%20the%20Indian%20corporate%20sector%20nearly%20quadrupled...%20Hiring%20and%20compensation%20growth%20hardly%20kept%20up%20with%20it.%20But%2C%20it%20is%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20companies%20to%20step%20up%20hiring%20and%20worker%20compensation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Economic%20Survey%20also%20underlined%20that%20many%20issues%20that%20influence%20economic%20growth%2C%20job%20creation%20and%20productivity%20lie%20in%20the%20domain%20of%20state%20governments.%20It%20called%20for%20a%20tripartite%20compact%20between%20the%20Centre%2C%20the%20states%20and%20the%20private%20sector%20%26quot%3Bto%20deliver%20on%20the%20higher%20and%20rising%20aspirations%20of%20Indians%20and%20complete%20the%20journey%20to%20Viksit%20Bharat%20by%202047%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20also%20found%20that%20economic%20shocks%20due%20to%20bad%20debts%20and%20the%20Covid%20pandemic%2C%20and%20not%20structural%20problems%2C%20influenced%20the%20country's%20employment%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Annual%20Survey%20of%20Unincorporated%20Enterprises%20for%202022-23%2C%20when%20compared%20with%20the%20results%20of%20the%20NSS%2073rd%20round%20of%20the%20'Key%20Indicators%20of%20Unincorporated%20Non-Agricultural%20Enterprises%20(Excluding%20Construction)%20in%20India'%20shows%20that%20overall%20employment%20in%20these%20enterprises%20fell%20from%2011.1%20crore%20in%202015-16%20to%2010.96%20crores.%20There%20was%20a%20reduction%20of%2054%20lakh%20workers%20in%20manufacturing%20but%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20workforce%20in%20trade%20and%20services%20gained%20in%20jobs%20limited%20the%20overall%20reduction%20in%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20in%20unincorporated%20enterprises%20to%20around%2016.45%20lakhs%20between%20these%20two%20periods.%20This%20comparison%20masks%20a%20big%20jump%20in%20manufacturing%20jobs%20that%20seems%20to%20have%20occurred%20between%202021-22%20(April%202021%20to%20March%202022)%20and%202022-23%20(October%202022%20to%20September%202023)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20survey%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20it%20said%2C%20suffered%20%26quot%3Btwo%20big%20economic%20shocks%20in%20quick%20succession%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BBad%20debts%20in%20the%20banking%20system%20and%20high%20corporate%20indebtedness%20were%20one.%20It%20took%20the%20first%20term%20of%20the%20present%20government%20and%20more%20to%20bring%20it%20under%20control.%20The%20Covid%20pandemic%20was%20the%20second%20shock%20and%20quickly%20followed%20the%20first%20one.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20conclude%20that%20the%20Indian%20economy's%20ability%20to%20create%20employment%20is%20structurally%20impaired.%20Nonetheless%2C%20going%20forward%2C%20the%20task%20is%20cut%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Economic%20Survey%20also%20underlined%20the%20geopolitical%20challenges%20India%20faces%20in%20its%20push%20to%20become%20a%20developed%20country.%20These%20include%20the%20advent%20of%20Artificial%20Intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%20the%20last%20Economic%20survey%20published%20in%20January%202023%20and%20this%20one%2C%20big%20changes%20are%20afoot%20in%20the%20geopolitical%20environment.%20The%20global%20backdrop%20for%20India's%20march%20towards%20Viksit%20Bharat%20in%202047%20could%20not%20be%20more%20different%20from%20what%20it%20was%20during%20the%20rise%20of%20China%20between%201980%20and%202015.%20Then%2C%20globalisation%20was%20at%20the%20cusp%20of%20its%20long%20expansion.%20Geopolitics%20was%20largely%20calm%20with%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20and%20Western%20powers%20welcomed%20and%20even%20encouraged%20the%20rise%20of%20China%20and%20its%20integration%20into%20the%20world%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConcerns%20over%20climate%20change%20and%20global%20warming%20were%20not%20so%20pervasive%20or%20grave%20then%20as%20they%20are%20now.%20Fourth%2C%20the%20advent%20of%C2%A0Artificial%20Intelligence%20casts%20a%20huge%20pall%20of%20uncertainty%20as%20to%20its%20impact%20on%20workers%20across%20all%20skill%20levels%20-%20low%2C%20semi%20and%20high.%20These%20will%20create%20barriers%20and%20hurdles%20to%20sustained%20high%20growth%20rates%20for%20India%20in%20the%20coming%20years%20and%20decades.%20Overcoming%20these%20requires%20a%20grand%20alliance%20of%20union%20and%20state%20governments%20and%20the%20private%20sector%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20survey%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntroducing%20the%20Economic%20Survey%20in%20Parliament%2C%20Finance%20Minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20said%20the%20Indian%20economy%20was%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20wicket%20and%20stable%20footing%26quot%3B%20and%20resilient%20in%20the%20face%20of%20geopolitical%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Indian%20economy%20is%20on%20a%20strong%20wicket%20and%20stable%20footing%20(and)%20demonstrating%20resilience%20in%20the%20face%20of%20geopolitical%20challenges.%20The%20economy%20has%20consolidated%20post-Covid%20recovery%20with%20policymakers%20-%20fiscal%20and%20monetary%20-%20ensuring%20economic%20and%20fi