a%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20do%20most%20of%20the%20cooking%20in%20the%20solar%20cookers%2C%20we%20have%20also%20kept%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(stove)%20as%20a%20backup%20for%20cloudy%20and%20rainy%20days.%20We%20collect%20firewood%20from%20trees%20around%20our%20house%20and%20also%20use%20coconut%20shells%20and%20cow%20dung%20cakes%20as%20fuel.%20We%20use%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eonly%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20backup%20for%20cooking%20that%20they%20use%20during%20cloudy%20days%20and%20at%20night%20is%20their%20stored%20solar%20energy.%20Their%20house%20has%20a%20small%20850%20VA%20solar%20inverter%20that%20delivers%20enough%20charge%20for%20low-wattage%20electrical%20appliances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20fondly%20talks%20about%20how%20she%20repurposed%20and%20converted%20an%20old%20box-type%20solar%20cooker%20into%20a%20food%20dehydrator.%20They%20use%20it%20to%20dehydrate%20and%20preserve%20excess%20fruits%20when%20they%20have%20a%20bounty.%20The%20contraption%20is%20also%20used%20for%20roasting%20grains%2C%20nuts%20and%20even%20drying%20homegrown%20turmeric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reva%20also%20dehydrates%20excess%20fruits%20in%20sunlight.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-357270%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EReva%20also%20dehydrates%20excess%20fruits%20in%20sunlight.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Reva%2C%20solar%20cooking%20is%20also%20cost-effective.%20%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20we%20would%20be%20getting%20the%20LPG%20cylinder%20refilled%20every%202-3%20months.%20It%20would%20cost%20Rs%201%2C200%20per%20refill.%20We%20invested%20Rs%2018%2C000%20for%20the%20solar%20cooker.%20This%20was%20a%20one-time%20investment%20as%20there%20is%20no%20other%20recurring%20expense%20and%20maintenance%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20households%20use%20LPG%20for%20cooking%20purposes%20and%20add%20to%20the%20emission%20burden.%20Reva%20urges%20people%20to%20harness%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F306168%2Findian-oil-indoor-solar-cooking-stove-surya-nutan-save-lpg-reduce-carbon-footprint%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar%20energy%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20is%20abundantly%20available%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20people%20think%20solar%20cooking%20is%20not%20convenient.%20With%20our%20experience%20of%20completely%20switching%20to%20solar%20cooking%2C%20we%20find%20it%20more%20convenient%20and%20easier%20than%20an%20LPG%20stove.%20Secondly%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20guilt-free%20cooking.%20There%20is%20an%20immense%20satisfaction%20knowing%20our%20food%20is%20cooked%20in%20sunlight%20effortlessly.%20We%20are%20not%20exploiting%20our%20planet%E2%80%99s%20resources%20anymore%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Reva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20managed%20to%20close%20this%20energy%20loop%20for%20ourselves.%20I